Author: (Bennett, 1828)
Remark: Date Eschmeyer, pers. comm. Based on juvenile form.

Author: (Bleeker, 1855)
Remark: Synonym of Halichoeres chrysotaenia according to Allen & Erdmann 2012:670 (Ref. 90102). This page will be removed.

Author: (Richardson, 1846)
Remark: Considered as a junior synonym of Pseudolabrus japonicus (Houttuyn, 1782) by Russell (1988) (Ref. 26203).

Author: (Macleay, 1881)
Remark: Species incertae sedis in Labridae according to Allen et al. (2006: Ref. 75154). This species is uncertain in Eschmeyer (CofF ver. Jul. 2010: Ref. 84883). Please send references, or more studies are needed.

Author: (Whitley, 1941)
Remark: Currently a synonym of Suezichthys gracilis (Steindachner & Döderlein, 1887), but probably is a distinct species (Barry Russell, pers. Comm, 11/07/13).

Author: (Linnaeus, 1758)
Remark: See nomenclatural details in Eschmeyer (CofF ver. Oct. 2012: Ref. 92135).

Author: (Lacepède, 1801)
Remark: Thalassoma fuscum (Lacepède, 1801) considered as a separate valid species in Dor 1984 (Ref. 2198) and CoF (Eschmeyer, 1998: Ref. 26282).

Author: (Bleeker, 1862)
Remark: This species supposedly described from Indonesia ("Java" as indicated in the name) is doubtful (Ref. 78585:157; Ref: 88079:30,37).  Please, send references or more studies are needed.

Author: Schultz, 1968
Remark: Issue on validity of subspecies: subspecies considered as valid in FB, elevated to species rank as Nicholsina collettei Schultz, 1968 in Eschmeyer (CofF ver. Mar. 2011: Ref. 86697). Please send references, or more studies are needed.

Author: (Valenciennes, 1840)
Remark: Issue on validity of subspecies: subspecies considered as valid in FB, elevated to species rank as Nicholsina usta (Valenciennes, 1840) in Eschmeyer (CofF ver. Mar. 2011: Ref. 86697). Please send references, or more studies are needed.
